{{Infobox organization | name = Nordic Association for American Studies | abbreviation = NAAS | motto = Scholarship, Teaching | formation = 1959 | founding_location = [[Oslo]] | region = [[Scandinavia]] | fields = [[American Studies]] | website = https://sites.google.com/site/naasstudies/home }}
The '''Nordic Association for American Studies''' (NAAS) is a scholarly society founded in 1959 which aims to promote [[American Studies|the study of the United States]] in the five [[Nordic countries]] and to facilitate communication between scholars interested in this field. Membership is open to individuals who live in or have a scholarly connection to [[Denmark]], [[Norway]], [[Sweden]], [[Finland]] or [[Iceland]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Scandinavia|first1=ASIS American Studies in|title=Nordic Association for American Studies|journal=American Studies in Scandinavia|date=1 September 1979|volume=11|issue=2|pages=81–83|url=https://rauli.cbs.dk/index.php/assc/article/view/1623/1653|accessdate=20 May 2018|language=en|format=PDF|issn=0044-8060}}</ref> The organization has five sub-organizations for each country and is, taken as a whole, a constituent member of [[The European Association for American Studies]]. It publishes the journal ''[[American Studies in Scandinavia]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=American Studies in Scandinavia|url=http://www.universitypress.dk/shop/subscribe-to-american-2768p.html|website=universitypress.dk|publisher=Syddansk Universitetsforlag|accessdate=20 May 2018}}</ref> and holds a conference every two years. It has so far arranged 25 conferences.<ref>{{cite web|title=Conferences - Nordic Association for American Studies (NAAS)|url=https://sites.google.com/site/naasstudies/conferences|website=sites.google.com|accessdate=20 May 2018}}</ref>
